# Conventional Commits
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Types:
# feat     – new feature
# fix      – bug fix
# docs     – documentation only
# style    – formatting, spacing, semicolons; no code change
# refactor – code restructure, no new features or fixes
# perf     – performance improvement
# test     – adding or updating tests
# chore    – maintenance, build, tooling, dependencies
#
# Rules:
# - Use imperative tense: "Add", "Fix", "Update"
# - Limit subject to ~50 characters, no period at end
# - Optional scope for module/feature: feat(auth), fix(cart)
# - Body (optional): explain WHAT and WHY, wrap at 72 chars
# - Footer (optional): references to issues, breaking changes
#
# Examples:
# feat(auth): add passwordless login via email
# fix(cart): correct total calculation for discounts
# docs(readme): update installation instructions
# style(ui): fix button alignment on homepage
# refactor(api): simplify user service logic
# perf(db): optimize query for orders
# test(order): add unit tests for order cancellation
# chore(deps): update Laravel to 12.5
